                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 11.658,
                                "byte_start": 89785,
                                "byte_stop": 136492,
                                "text": "Justice Alito has the opinion this morning in case 05-1429, Travelers Casualty \u0026 Surety versus Pacific Gas \u0026 Electric Co."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 11.658,
                        "stop": 222.877,
                        "byte_start": 136492,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15068,
                            "name": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/samuel_alito_jr",
                            "last_name": "Alito",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2712,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 1138687200,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "George W. Bush",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2712"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32684,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 44799,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/samuel_a_alito_jr_1.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 3531,
                            "identifier": "samuel_alito_jr"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 11.658,
                                "stop": 17.657,
                                "byte_start": 136492,
                                "byte_stop": 160420,
                                "text": "Now this case comes to us writ of certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 17.657,
                                "stop": 30.604,
                                "byte_start": 160420,
                                "byte_stop": 212247,
                                "text": "The question before us is whether a Federal Bankruptcy Law precludes recovery of attorney\u2019s fees authorized by contract based solely on the fact does fees were incurred litigating issues of Bankruptcy Law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 30.604,
                                "stop": 34.501,
                                "byte_start": 212247,
                                "byte_stop": 227816,
                                "text": "We hope but it does not and therefore vacate and remand."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 34.501,
                                "stop": 42.735,
                                "byte_start": 227816,
                                "byte_stop": 260730,
                                "text": "Respondent Pacific Gas and Electric Company (PG\u0026E) filed for chapter 11 Bankruptcy in April, 2001."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 42.735,
                                "stop": 56.971,
                                "byte_start": 260730,
                                "byte_stop": 317677,
                                "text": "Petitioner Travelers Casualty \u0026 Surety Company of America which previously issued a Surety bond to guarantee PG\u0026E\u2019s payment of state workers\u2019 compensation benefits filed the claim in the bankruptcy case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 56.971,
                                "stop": 74.308,
                                "byte_start": 317677,
                                "byte_stop": 387058,
                                "text": "To protect itself against the possibility of default by PG\u0026E with the Bankruptcy Courts approval PG\u0026E eventually agreed to insert language into its reorganization plan and disclosure statement to protect Travelers in the event of such a default."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 74.308,
                                "stop": 96.783,
                                "byte_start": 387058,
                                "byte_stop": 476920,
                                "text": "Additional litigation over the negotiated language nevertheless ensued and result ultimately resolved by a court-approved stipulation stating among other things that Travelers could assert a general unsecured claim for attorney\u2019s fees incurred during the bankruptcy proceedings as authorized by the party\u2019s original indemnity agreements."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 96.783,
                                "stop": 100.644,
                                "byte_start": 476920,
                                "byte_stop": 492384,
                                "text": "Travelers then field an amended claim seeking attorney\u2019s fees."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 100.644,
                                "stop": 116.215,
                                "byte_start": 492384,
                                "byte_stop": 554660,
                                "text": "PG\u0026E objected to that claim based on the Ninth Circuit\u2019s rule originally announced in that courts decision and in In re Fobian that attorney\u2019s fees may not be awarded in connection with the litigation of issues of Federal Bankruptcy Law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 116.215,
                                "stop": 125.107,
                                "byte_start": 554660,
                                "byte_stop": 590291,
                                "text": "The bankruptcy court rejected travelers claim based on the Fobian rule and the District Court and the Ninth Circuit affirmed on the same basis."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 125.107,
                                "stop": 129.681,
                                "byte_start": 590291,
                                "byte_stop": 608577,
                                "text": "We granted certiorari to resolve the conflict in the Lower Court on this issue."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 129.681,
                                "stop": 133.519,
                                "byte_start": 608577,
                                "byte_stop": 623937,
                                "text": "Today we conclude that the Fobian rule is unsound."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 133.519,
                                "stop": 142.677,
                                "byte_start": 623937,
                                "byte_stop": 660508,
                                "text": "Under the American rule the prevailing litigant is normally not entitled to collect attorney\u2019s fees from the loser that rule can however be overcome by statute."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 142.677,
                                "stop": 147.068,
                                "byte_start": 660508,
                                "byte_stop": 678063,
                                "text": "It can also be overcome by contract even in bankruptcy proceedings."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 147.068,
                                "stop": 152.636,
                                "byte_start": 678063,
                                "byte_stop": 700423,
                                "text": "So long as the contract is in enforceable under substantive Non-Bankruptcy Law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 152.636,
                                "stop": 162.146,
                                "byte_start": 700423,
                                "byte_stop": 738458,
                                "text": "A claim for fees based on an otherwise enforceable contract is allowable in bankruptcy except for bankruptcy law provides otherwise."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 162.146,
                                "stop": 176.765,
                                "byte_start": 738458,
                                "byte_stop": 796867,
                                "text": "Section 502(b) of the Bankruptcy Code provides the Bankruptcy Court \u201cshall allow\u201d a creditors\u2019 claim \u201cexcept to the extent that\u201d the claim implicates any of the nine exceptions enumerated in that Section."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 176.765,
                                "stop": 194.016,
                                "byte_start": 796867,
                                "byte_stop": 865935,
                                "text": "None of those exceptions mandates or even supports the denial of the contract based claim for attorney\u2019s fees based solely on the fact that the issues litigated involved issues of bankruptcy law nor does any other provision of the Bankruptcy Code support such rule."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 194.016,
                                "stop": 207.146,
                                "byte_start": 865935,
                                "byte_stop": 918389,
                                "text": "In concluding otherwise the Court of Appeals relied exclusively on its own precedent most notably Fobian that precedent however finds no support in and affirmatively conflicts with Federal Bankruptcy Law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 207.146,
                                "stop": 215.08,
                                "byte_start": 918389,
                                "byte_stop": 950154,
                                "text": "PG\u0026E raises several arguments suggesting that Travelers claim might fail even in the absences of Fobian rule."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 215.08,
                                "stop": 220.615,
                                "byte_start": 950154,
                                "byte_stop": 972306,
                                "text": "But because those arguments are not fairly included within the question before us we will not address that."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 220.615,
                                "stop": 222.877,
                                "byte_start": 972306,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The court\u2019s opinion is unanimous."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
